question:
What will be the output of the following C++ code?

```cpp
#include <iostream>
using namespace std;

int main() {
    int x = 10;
    if (x > 5)
        cout << "Greater";
    else
        cout << "Smaller";
    return 0;
}
```

What is wrong with the following C++ if statement?

```cpp
if x > 10 {
    cout << "Hello";
}
```

What will be the output of the following C++ code?

```cpp
#include <iostream>
using namespace std;

int main() {
    int x = 5;
    if (x == 5)
        cout << "Yes";
    cout << "No";
    return 0;
}
```
